The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 World Briefs

 Hospital horror 

 Baghdad, Nov. 24 (Reuters): A car bomb blew up outside a hospital where Iraqi police were gathered in a town south of Baghdad today, killing 31 people, police said. 

 The explosives-packed car was parked in front of the hospital in Mahmoudiya, just south of Baghdad, and blew up after two patrols of Iraqi police pulled up outside. 

 Putin backing 

 Moscow (Reuters): Russian President Vladimir Putin threw his weight on Thursday behind a draft bill that human rights groups say will restrict their work. 

 Bangla alert 

 Dhaka (Reuters): Bangladesh has warned foreign missions about the threat of possible attacks by Islamist militants. 

 UK veil ban 

 London (AFP): A British University college has banned students from wearing Islamic veils and hooded sweatshirts in an effort to improve security. 




